quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  8,1,"They ask you concerning spoils of war. Say, “Spoils are at the disposal of God and the messenger. So be conscious of God, and keep the relations between yourselves straight. And follow God and His messenger, if you do believe.”"
  8,2,"The believers are those who, when God is mentioned, feel a tremble in their hearts, and when they hear His signs rehearsed, find their faith strengthened, and put all their trust in their Lord"
  8,3,They establish prayer and give out of the gifts We have given them for sustenance
  8,4,"Such in truth are the believers. They have degrees of dignity with their Lord, forgiveness and generous sustenance"
  8,5,"Your Lord ordered you out of your house in truth, even though a group among the believers disliked it"
  8,6,"They disputing with you concerning the truth after it was made clear, as if they were being driven to death and they saw it"
  8,7,"Behold, God promised that one of the two enemy groups would be yours. You wished that the one unarmed would be yours, but God willed to justify the truth according to His words, and to cut off the roots of the unbelievers"
  8,8,"That He might justify truth and prove falsehood false, distasteful as it is to those guilty"